task.summary: Default task
Changed label on pilot edit dialog button from 'Edit' to 'Save'
Added Team results in Results Manager
Changed Team Name in Pilot editor to AutoComplete
Updated release version
Added Support for HC-05 Bluetooth External Display, Added status icons for specific drivers & Ext Display
Added menu item to invoke the round timeout dialog on demand
Fixed issue where round timeout was not starting after an aborted flight
Fixed issue where driver was being stopped on screen rotation
Added preference to choose device for hc-05 input source
Hid usb & BT options when demo mode is selected
Fixed UI not updating when Ext Display device changed in settings
Added line breaks after external results json broadcast
Added Import from f3xvault
Added f3xvault ID values
Bug Fixes
Fixed ordering of pilots in the csv output for spreadsheet
Updated readme with latest release
Rewrite non alphanumeric chars in filename

new features: -added new input source for socket connection via USB Tethering to our Raspberry Pi (named TcpIoService) -changed web layout to a simplistic black and white look - like a sheet of paper with tables on it (menu structure is still similar) -added web page with live information (flying pilot, fastest time, current flight time, estimated flight time and more) -added web page with start list -added web page with overall results in one table -incorporated wind sensor data -show in Titlebar and on live web page in a userfriendly format -speech notification when wind speed or direction is illegal regarding the FAI rules -usage and parameters are configurable in settings dialog -import all pilots and race configuration data (predefined start list with groups and rounds, ...) from/to csv file -added FilteredFilePickerActivity to only see compatible files (*.json and *.csv) on import -show current IP in settings for accessing the results server -show group in results dialogs -added functionality for hardware button triggering "score current flight zero and interrupt the automatic to start the next pilot afterwards" -added functionality for hardware button awarding penalties (accompanied by new beep sound) -added finish Race button in next round dialog -added button for rotate shuffle to the add pilots dialog -automatically accept flight time of a finished flight automatically after 5 seconds of inactivity and move on to the next pilot -added com.amitshekhar.android:debug-db:1.0.1 for database debugging at runtime (adds readout/editing on a web page through a dedicated socket connection) -added start_pos and group_nr and points to racetimes database table to simplify internal start order handling/changing and group handling for pilots and web results displaying
bugfixes: -don't overwrite volume setting (with to maximum), so that it can be adjusted to the preferred setting by the user -setting voice synthesis options in settings dialog didn't work correctly and caused crashes when set from within race -added a country code definition json file to be able to derive the [default/initial] TTS language from the Locale -on/off course not displayed in RaceTimerFrag4 on late entry -use SoundPool instead of mediaplayer to decrease buzzer sound latency -fixed NullPointerException in RaceActivity List rendering -limit RaceResultsServer socket connections and set MIN_PRIOTRITY to prevent overload and disturbance of RaceTimerActivity -customized some german translations -fixed race start_number and offset processing
made TcpIoService connect IP configurable
only mark pilot as retired in round, when there is no time and status is retired, because status is only valid for current round
reformatted race title and round title
fixed: pref_usb_tether was not used
-don't allow creating empty races (NullPointerExceptions) -reset the race timeout when deleting a race to invalidate the timer for a new race created with that same id
added web page for team results
show when no teams defined
consider last completed round when the race is finished on the leaderboard
added a method for checking if the round is complete
fixed some bugs in round complete detection in Results and ResultsCompletedRoundsActivity
-added menu entry for finishing the race -changed some translations
added menu for finishing the race
minor fix

-fixed some inconsistent retired pilot info displayed on results web page -removed pilot status from racetimes serialization for results web page (was redundant) -send untruncated points to results web page js to make overall score calculation most accurate -update IP address shown in race title -nicer team results pilot table formatting

-always keep pilot.start_pos valid -refactored js table cell creation -fixed that race title is alternating between multiple titles when you entered different races -removed jquery dependencies from liveinfo.js
fixed: pref_usb_tether was not used
added option to select results server style
added option to select results server style
added option to select results server style
-merged changes from mark -made results server style configurable -some bugfixes
default results website: included last round in points calculation, when race is finished
deactivated wind warning announcement in CD language, because switching TTS language when a pilot is flying could delay crucial announcements (like the count down of climb out time)
-made extended JSON export/import format configurable -fixed bug in export/import file format (json/csv) selection dialog
-fixed bug in JSOn import
